From 90683d09e54551b913c901bd322efa9e4de04c01 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alex Angel <aangeletakis@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 07:12:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] [clang] std::fetch: forward --fetch-allow to the cc1 compile
 job

The flag was only forwarded in ClangAs::ConstructJob (the assembler job),
so ordinary compiles dropped it with -Wunused-command-line-argument and
every __builtin_std_fetch came back NotAuthorized against an empty
allow-list. Forward it where --embed-dir= already goes:
Clang::AddPreprocessingOptions, which feeds the real cc1 job.

Caught by the fetch smoke test in the embed repo's remote build.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Clang.cpp | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Clang.cpp b/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Clang.cpp
index ce0f5c9a9..e03a6c445 100644
--- a/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Clang.cpp
+++ b/clang/lib/Driver/ToolChains/Clang.cpp
@@ -1108,7 +1108,8 @@ void Clang::AddPreprocessingOptions(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
 
   Args.addAllArgs(CmdArgs,
                   {options::OPT_D, options::OPT_U, options::OPT_I_Group,
-                   options::OPT_F, options::OPT_embed_dir_EQ});
+                   options::OPT_F, options::OPT_embed_dir_EQ,
+                   options::OPT_fetch_allow_EQ});
 
   // Add -Wp, and -Xpreprocessor if using the preprocessor.
 
-- 
